The Big Conservation Lie book was launched on Tuesday at the University of Nairobi main campus.The book is a combined effort of two authors; Conservation Solutions Afrika director Mordecai Ogada and veteran journalist Johu Mbaria. The book focuses on Kenya's historical injustices and the destruction of wildlife habitat over the years.Those present at the event were National Land Commission's Zachariah Ndege, UoN's Professor Nicholas Oguge, Colorado State University Associate Professor Brett Bruyere and Community Museums of Kenya's Eustace Gitonga.